column5: Looking to have some prop work done on a stainless prop, anybody know of anyone close to Orangeville?Newmarket area that works on them.  I'm looking to have it fixed up a little and a little pitch removed  Thanks

I don't know of anyone in our area or even in Canada but a lot of praise is given to Mark Croxton at Mark's high performance propeller.  He has a tech sheet listed on his website and the more information you give him, the better the prop will turn out.  His website is http://marksprops.com and the praise he gets in BassBoat Central is rediculous. A few guys in the ottawa area have had him work their props and have been extremely happy. If there is something you want done to a prop, he can do it and all of his prices are listed on his website.  Adam
